Bank account number, your name on bank passbook and IFSC code of the bank;
PAN card number, Aadhar card number(redacted), KYC related information either through videos or other online/ offline verification documents as per the mandate from banking /financial institutes offering the financial product, regulatory guidelines or to comply with such other directions of relevant regulatory authorities , for the Services you shall be utilizing (purpose of investments & transactions) and your business-related information.
Employment related details (e.g. occupation, income, employer details, designation) as part of our record retention for Central KYC Records Registry (CKYCR) purposes under Prevention of Money Laundering (Maintenance of Records) Rules, 2005
Access to your device camera, device microphone, device information (including storage, model, mobile network information, device type, IP Address and location (to capture precise and/or coarse location), device unique identifier for various purpose in relation to onboarding on Platform, KYC verification, fraud prevention, security and compliance requirement.
On the basis your specific consent, we may access your contact list specifically for enabling you with payment related services and for UPI services and will not extend it to any digital lending activities.
We may seek for certain financial and transactional information such as payment information i.e method , mode and manner of payment , credit / debit card information , card type , expiry date on the credit or debit card , name on the card , billing address, transaction information such as date of transaction , transaction amount , transaction history , and related details, debit instructions and / or standing instructions for processing payments for various bill payment services you have opted for;
We may access, store, transfer, and process your SMS data based on your explicit consent. This is required to facilitate financial transactions such as payments, OTPs for logins, security verification, bill payments, recharge reminders, and other related services, ensuring seamless and secure functionality
For certain financial services offered by our partner(s), to comply with regulatory direction(s) and for security purpose(s), we may request our Users to permit us to link their mobile device(s), and SIM with their account for device binding purpose. We ensure that User(s) prior and explicit permission is sought, to perform device binding by pushing SMS through your device. Post verification, User’s device will become a registered device. In case of change of device, User will be required to re-login and re-authorize itself on its device.
Browser plug-ins, and cookies or similar technologies that may identify your browser Application and plug-ins, notifications etc..
