Enter the information manually
: You provide investment details like scheme name, investment type, investment date and investment value by manually entering the data whenever necessary / applicable.
Employees Provident Fund Passbook (“
EPF passbook
”) details:
You can choose to provide explicit consent to INDmoney to collect this information from https://passbook.epfindia.gov.in/MemberPassBook/Login, by providing your 12-digit Universal Account Number, assigned to you as a member of EPFO, and the related password. Your EPFO password will be stored by INDmoney at a local device in encrypted format and will be stored on our server in encrypted format. We use AWS Key Management Service Feature for storing your EPFO password. This will enable INDmoney to consolidate and present your comprehensive EPF passbook data. This will also help you to get an accurate picture of your overall investment details on your INDmoney dashboard.
National Pension Scheme (“
NPS-Tier I
”) statement details:
You can choose to provide explicit consent to INDmoney to collect this information from your NPS-Tier I statement assigned to you as a member of NPS-Tier I, and the related password to open the NPS Tier I statement. Your NPS-Tier I statement password will be stored by INDmoney at a local device in encrypted format and will be stored on our server in encrypted format. We use AWS Key Management Service Feature for storing your NPS-Tier I statement password. This will enable INDmoney to consolidate and present your comprehensive NPS-Tier I data as well as provide tax saving advisory which includes NPS. This will also help you to get an accurate picture of your overall investment details on your INDmoney dashboard.
You can choose to de-track NPS-Tier I Investments anytime from the NPS-Tier I Investments section or by writing to
privacy@indmoney.com
.
GOOGLE ACCOUNT EMAILS (GMAIL):
The User may also choose to provide explicit consent to connect/integrate the User’s Gmail account(s) with his/her account on the Platform. You can also choose to integrate Your one or more of email accounts by connecting such account(s) with Your account on the Platform. The following are the information collected from Your consented email accounts:
The attachments from the senders who have the details of your financials investments or spends such as folio numbers, transaction dates, Redemption Amounts, income tax document like ITR, your credit card, statements, spends. INDmoney organizes this information in your account to provide deep analytics and other services.
We access your Gmail account, only basis your explicit consent for auto tracking your investments & spends in order to effectively help you in organizing your financial life. We will only be accessing and analyzing the contents of emails (including the attachments) consisting of ‘read-only’ in a secured manner. You can choose to grant your explicit consent to connect your Gmail account with INDmoney account (using Google’s OAuth authentication method).
The benefit of opting to connect Your Gmail account is that your both investment and expense information gets updated automatically every month. Given the updated information, the application can hence give you deep and accurate analytics on your net worth and to curate best offers for you to avail various financial products / services via our Platform.
You can anytime choose to de-link your Gmail account with the application at any time and/ or you can delete your information by writing to
privacy@indmoney.com
,
support@indmoney.com
Please note that such data obtained by this integration will be used by the Company solely for providing the Services and for improving the User experience pertaining to the features of the Platform.
